16/05/2004
ZAGREB, Croatia -- President Stipe Mesic met with the Croatian member of Bosnia and Herzegovina's (BiH) trilateral presidency, Dragan Covic on Friday (14 May).
They discussed the need for measures to intensify economic relations as well as issues related to refugee returns.
Covic called on all Bosnian Croat refugees currently residing in Croatia to return to their pre-war homes, particularly refugees from Republika Srpska.
During the visit to Zagreb, Covic also met with Prime Minister Ivo Sanader, who stressed his country's full support for BiH's bid to join NATO's Partnership for Peace programme.
(RTRS, NTV Hayat - 14/05/04)
